claims:
3. The chimeric antigen receptor according to claim 2, wherein
the CD64a extracellular domain comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 1;
the CD64b extracellular domain comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 2;
the CD32a extracellular domain comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 3;
the CD32b extracellular domain comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 4;
the CD16a extracellular domain comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 5; and
the CD16b extracellular domain comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 6.

8. The chimeric antigen receptor according to claim 1, wherein the chimeric antigen receptor further comprises a Linker region between the antigen binding domain and the transmembrane domain;
preferably, the Linker region comprises a Hinge region and an IgG constant region, wherein the IgG constant region comprises CH2 and/or CH3;
preferably, the Hinge region comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 12;
preferably, the CH2 comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 13;
preferably, the CH3 comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 14;
preferably, the chimeric antigen receptor further comprises a signal peptide, wherein the signal peptide comprises any one of a GM-CSF signal peptide, an IL-2 signal peptide, a CD8α signal peptide or an IL-6 signal peptide;
preferably, the GM-CSF signal peptide comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 15;
preferably, the IL-2 signal peptide comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 16;
preferably, the CD8α signal peptide comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 17;
preferably, the IL-6 signal peptide comprises an amino acid sequence as shown in SEQ ID NO: 18.

10. An expression vector, comprising the nucleic acid molecule according to claim 9;
preferably, the expression vector comprises a viral vector; and
preferably, the viral vector comprises any one of a lentiviral vector, a retroviral vector or an adeno-associated viral vector, preferably a lentiviral vector.

14. A pharmaceutical composition, comprising any one or a combination of at least two of the chimeric antigen receptor according claim 1, the nucleic acid molecule, the expression vector, the recombinant lentivirus or the chimeric antigen receptor T cell ; wherein the nucleic acid molecule encodes the chimeric antigen receptor, the expression vector comprising the nucleic acid molecule, and the chimeric antigen receptor T cell expresses the chimeric antigen receptor;
preferably, the pharmaceutical composition further comprises an antibody drug;
preferably, the pharmaceutical composition comprises an antibody containing an IgG1 and/or IgG3 Fc fragment;
preferably, the antibody drug comprises any one or a combination of at least two of rituximab monoclonal antibody, anti-CD20 monoclonal antibody, trastuzumab monoclonal antibody, cetuximab monoclonal antibody, edrecolomab monoclonal antibody, nimotuzumab monoclonal antibody or a gemtuzumab ozogamicin monoclonal antibody;
preferably, the pharmaceutical composition further comprises any one or a combination of at least two of a pharmaceutically acceptable carrier, an excipient or a diluent.
